rooms.Name: Outside a guard station
rooms.Description:
You have come across a small guard station at a bend in the path.  There is
a small booth right off the path to the west, and an armed guard is standing
in the center of the path before you.  You are free to go back the way you 
came.

Exits.Description:
Past the Imperial Scout, you see a pathway leading through the desert and
towards some metal building.
A small booth with the door slightly open.

rooms.Name: Along the sandy pathway..
rooms.Description:
As you begin walking down the path you hear a curious sound coming from
behind you.  You turn to see what is making the noise, and watch as your 
footsteps slowly disappear, erased by a hot desert wind which pushes the
immense dunes before it.  It appears you can't go back the way you came,
so you push onwards to the north, and towards the strange metal structure
ahead.

Exits.Description:
There is a large sand dune ahead of you, you think you can climb it and
see what's ahead.

rooms.Name: On top of a sand dune..
rooms.Description:
You stumble on top of the dune and try to balance yourself.  You look out
over the land and see a man dressed in white armor guarding the large
building ahead of you.  Not paying much attention, you lose your footing
and slip to the bottom of the dune.  Immediately you hear a gutteral snarling
coming from behind you.. perhaps you've disturbed something's sleep?  Not
wanting to find out, you rush towards the building, hoping to escape.

Exits.Description:
You see a large building about 50 yards away.. and the snarling sounds
coming from behind you seem to be getting louder and louder.. so you
run onwards towards the building seeking safety.

Looking back from where you came, you notice your footprints keep getting
blown away, which leads you to believe something is amiss.

rooms.Name: Outside the Large Building
rooms.Description:
You are standing at the entrance to a 40 foot tall structure composed of
steel. A large door blocks your entry, guarded by another Imperial Scout.
There is a keypad next to the door and a slot next to the keypad about
half a hand long.  Overall the place looks pretty shabby.

Exits.Description:
You see a large metal door with a keypad beside it.  On the door are written
in large red letters :

     IMPERIAL OUTPOST GARRISON #42 - AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY!!

There's a keypad with a slot on the side for a keycard to unlock the door
with, however, only the guards are trusted with such an item.
Yep.  Same ol' sand dune you just slipped down off of.

ExtraDescs.Description:
There's a slot next to the door which would probably give you access if only
you had the keycard that accessed it.  Perhaps some guard might have it.

A large steel portal, you doubt that you could get through it without
a key...

rooms.Name: Inside the Imperial Bunker
rooms.Description:
You have entered a large, carpeted room.  Judging from the rough, Spartan
furnishings this room was not decorated with comfort in mind... it has a
decidedly military  flavor.   Long metal benches line the west wall.  A spiral
staircase leads up into another room in the far corner.  Doors lead into other
parts of the bunker to the east and north and another leads back out into the 
desert to the south.

Exits.Description:
D0
You see a room full of large, yellow maintenance droids and lifters doing
various tasks.  There's a passageway leading up, where you can't tell from 
here, however.

You see a room cluttered with large oil drums and spare parts scatter the
place.
Yep.  Same ol' doorway you just walked through.

You see a spiral staircase leading up into a hole in the ceiling.  From the
hole you can hear a loud radio blarring away landing instructions in some
mechanical drone.

rooms.Name: The Control Tower
rooms.Description:
Imperial craft are guided to the outpost's landing pad from this large room.
In fact, you can see a large shuttle out the window on the north wall.  A
large droid stands by the computer consoles ready to guide any unexpected
Imperial craft safely in.  On one wall is an empty rack for blasters.
Very few weapons of this kind are kept at such a backwater outpost.

Exits.Description:
You see a metal door with a label saying, "Joe Bob Fred, Controller of 
Imperial Outpost #42." You notice the panel beside the door is flashing in
red letters, "OPEN"

You see a man staring into a video screen display, as he punches the keys on
his computer. Surrounding him are various mechanical looking things which, 
suffice to say, are used for communicating with incoming ships.
Down the spiral staircase you see the same lobby you left just a while ago.

ExtraDescs.Description:
A large sign covers the door saying in large red letters :

NO UNAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL!!

KEEP OUT!! THIS MEANS YOU!!

rooms.Name: Communications Room
rooms.Description:
Large satellite communications panels line three walls of this compact room.
A wiry young man in deep gray sits in a swiveling chair before one of
these huge panels.  Lights and monitors wink on and off at random seeming
periods of time.  The recruit doesn't notice that you are standing here.  
He is much too busy watching the incoming picture from a probe droid.

Exits.Description: You see a room manned by a large black droid guiding ships in.

rooms.Name: The Post Commander's Office
rooms.Description:
This room though small has been richly decorated.  The rich decor
doesn't hide the fact that the commander of the post is a career officer
of the  Imperial Fleet.  A large metal desk and uncomfortable chair sit
in one corner and a large metal bookshelf full of Imperial policy
manuals stands against the other wall.

Exits.Description: You see a large hallway.

rooms.Name: Departure Zone / Arrival Area
rooms.Description:
Large load lifters and carts of supplies are parked in yellow striped
patches scattered evenly around the floor of this wide room.  There are
no humans in sight, as this outpost is mostly maintained by droids doing
99 percent of the manual labor.  Leading up is a ladder onto the main launch
platform.  A small machine lies here discarded in the corner, it 
looks like it's a token machine/shuttle pass vendor.

Exits.Description: Yep. Same ol' carpeted lobby as it was when you last left it.
You see the access ramp to an Imperial Lamba Class Shuttle.

rooms.Name: The Fuel Storage Room
rooms.Description:
Large drums of fuel are stacked with military precision along the north
and south walls of the room.  This is where Imperial ships get the fuel
they need to get back into space.  Between the rows of fuel drums,
leaning against the east wall of the storage room, is a large Imperial
probe droid.

Exits.Description: Yep. Same ol' carpeted lobby as it was when you last left it.

rooms.Name: Inside the guardhouse
rooms.Description:
From the look of things, the guards are pretty lax in their duties.
Empty food containers share a tabletop with some communication gear.
Another guard is standing here, looking at a wall monitor.

Exits.Description: You can exit the guard booth to the east.

rooms.Name: The Mos Eisley Customs Office
rooms.Description:
This small building has been converted by the Empire into a bureaucratic
office complex.  Starship captains pay the local customs and excise taxes
here when they are in port.  Of course the starship captains who frequent
Mos Eisley are not notorious for actually paying these taxes, most of them
being involved in smuggling operations.  Local bureaucrats sit behind
desks shuffling paperwork.  In the corner lies a small token
machine for purchasing passes for the ride back from Tatooine.

Exits.Description: You see a dusty roadway leading east into the desert.

rooms.Name: Orleon Lane
rooms.Description:
This is the northern end of Orleon Lane.  Buildings of all shapes and sizes
crowd around.  To the northwest is Docking Bay 94.  West of here is a 
deserted and abused building which houses the Mos Eisley Customs Office.
To the south is the Spaceport Inn, the most lavish place in the town. 
A well used path leads out into the desert to the north, and Orlean Lane
continues to the east.

Exits.Description: A well used path leads into the desert from here.

You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle of the road.  Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd.  The big sale is about to begin!

You see a large, ornately decorated building with huge sand-sculptures 
standing outside the building.  A sign in front of it invites you to enter
and lay your weary bones to rest.

You see a decrepit building, on the verge of collapsing.  On the side of the
building is a sign reading: Mo Eis ley S  cepo t Cus oms Of ice.  You gather
that the sandstorms are really bad here and have eroded much of the building.
You see a large docking bay with the Millenium Falcon parked there.

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 94
rooms.Description:
Docking Bay 94 is one of the less frequented ones in town.  It is on
the very outskirts of Mos Eisley so a large number of the captains 
who do use it are smugglers.  A large, irregularly shaped freighter
has been left here.  It's markings match those of the 'Millenium 
Falcon' which is piloted by the fabled Han Solo.  A huge gun
covers your every move from the shadows under the Falcon.
Orleon Lane lies to the southeast.

Exits.Description: You can exit back to Orleon Lane.

rooms.Name: The Mos Eisley Market Square
rooms.Description:
You stand on the Market Square of the spaceport Mos Eisley.  Blocky one-
story buildings with walls of thick white adobe surround the Square on all
sides. To the north you can hear the mechanical noises of a large  Moisture
Vaporizer. South is Lup's General Store, a good place to get supplies of many
sorts for life on this bleak, desert planet.  The Spaceport Rentals building 
is in a squat building to the southwest.  Sounds of music and drinking float
from the large, underground Cantina, tempting you to spend your gold in
its cool recesses.

Exits.Description:
You see good ol' "Drizzle" McGee, the town's watersupply expert.  He's been
selling water to the town for years now, since he's the only one who knows
how to keep the Water Vaporizer operating during the harsh sandstorms.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

You see a small shack with a small sign on it that reads:

                Lup's General Store

                Stop in and buy something...
Orleon Lane continues to the west.

You see a large, domed structure halfway buried into the earth.  From the
opening you hear loud piping music.  Some drunken stormtroopers stagger out
of the opening and walk down the alleyway.  This must be the galaxy-famous
Cantina.

You see an alcove containing many broken, old junkheaps.  These vehicles
are no longer working, however you could probably find some surplus parts
for your landspeeder or perhaps your sky hopper.

rooms.Name: The Spaceport Inn
rooms.Description:
This lobby is a wide room, well-lit by large, energy-efficient sealed windows.
A cool breeze runs through the room from the many air conditioning vents set
into the walls.  This is one of the most comfortable places on the planet, and
is used primarily by rich off-world traders who are unused to (and unwilling
to adapt to) the local climate.

Exits.Description: To the north, you see Orleon Lane.

You see a red-carpeted floor leading to the Manager's office.  You'd probably
have to talk to him if you'd like to stay here for a long time.  He might
give you an OFFER and you could RENT.  He's known to deal in cryogenic
stasis, perhaps you should talk to him.

rooms.Name: The Spaceport Inn - Managerial Office
rooms.Description:
Lush red carpets cover the floors of these offices.  Clerks sit behind
heavy desks, made from polished, off-world wood.  No one notices your
silent arrival.  A door in the north wall leads back to the main lobby.

Exits.Description:
You see the lobby. Yep, that's it. I'm tired of writing these things..., it's
not like you're reading them... or are you?

You see a large, steel door that's locked.  Maybe someone has the key around
in this hotel somewhere?

rooms.Name: A Small Alcove Full of Junk
rooms.Description:
You are in a large alcove filled with all manner of junk.  Jawas 
wander through the piled equipment searching for equipment that 
they can salvage and sell later to landholders out in the  desert.  
Many of the items to be found here, however, are far beyond a
fixable state.

Exits.Description:
You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle or the road. Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd. The big sale is about to begin!

rooms.Name: Lup's General Store
rooms.Description:
Dusty shelves adorn this room, all of which are covered with items of every
sort, from junk items to valuable desert equipment.  Hearing the bell ring
as you enter, Tar Lup, the store's owner, comes out to see how he can serve
you.  Through a door to the north, you can go into the Mos Eisley Market
Square.

Exits.Description:
You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle or the road. Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd. The big sale is about to begin!

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Cantina
rooms.Description:
You enter the Cantina, happy to escape the harsh sun for as long as you
can. The entryway is light and hot, mainly because of the large doors
in the northwest and east walls.  The think white plaster walls do,
however, block out enough heat to make this room bearable.  You can hear
the unmistakable sounds of drinking and singing down the short staircase
into the main room of the Cantina.

Exits.Description:
You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints. Probably because of the 
numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.
You see a set of steps leading down into the loud cantina.

You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle of the road.  Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd.  The big sale is about to begin!

rooms.Name: Moisture Vaporator
rooms.Description:
This is the main water 'plant' of Mos Eisley.  Water is collected all
over the deserts of Tatooine, and brought here to be distributed to
the citizens. Technically, Vapor Technicians are not supposed to sell
the water to strangers.. but old Drizzle knows about the piles of forms
a non-citizen must go through to obtain water here, so he sells it on
the side. (for a *very* hefty price of course.)

Exits.Description:
You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle of the road. Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd. The big sale is about to begin!

rooms.Name: Orleon Lane
rooms.Description:
Orleon Lane takes a sharp bend from its easterly course here.  A huge
building towers over the road to the east and north.  This is the building
where Imperial craft are kept when they make their infrequent visits
to the planet.  Orleon Lane runs west and south from here.

Exits.Description:
You see a large docking bay.  From there you can buy a way off this 
dusty planet.

You see a large docking bay.  From there you can buy a way off this 
dusty planet.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

You see a crowded marketplace set up in the middle of the road.  Loud shouts
are heard from within the crowd.  The big sale is about to begin!

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 86
rooms.Description:
You enter the shaded entrance to Docking Bay 86.  An Imperial check point
has been set up in the doorway to block curious intruders.  As you enter
a squad of stormtroopers turns and looks your way.  Soon one of them
will come over to see what it is that you want.  Many different types of
Imperial ships are parked here... most of them are Tie Fighters though.
Orleon Lane is to the south and more of Docking Bay 86 lies to the east.

Exits.Description: Docking Bay 86 continues to your east.   Yes, it's REALLY that big.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 86
rooms.Description:
You are at the far back corner of Docking Bay 86.  Ships scheduled 
for immediate departure are moved here just before take-off.  A 
shiny Lambda class Imperial shuttle is sitting on the pad here fueled 
and ready  to lift off.  The two entrances to Docking Bay 86 lie to the
south and west.

Exits.Description: Docking Bay 86 continues to your south.   Yes, it's REALLY that big.
Docking Bay 86 continues to your west.   Yes, it's REALLY that big.

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 86
rooms.Description:
Docking Bay 86 is the biggest one in town.  Imperial ships are stored 
here when they stop on this tiny planet.  Many different ships line 
the walls  in neat rows.  An old, battered freighter catches your 
attention from its spot along the east wall... it was the one that you
arrived here in.  An  Imperial patrol is just to the north so you had
best leave before they  find you tampering with the ships.

Exits.Description: Docking Bay 86 continues to your north.   Yes, it's REALLY that big.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

rooms.Name: Orleon Lane
rooms.Description:
The whine of thrusters drifts from the east where one of the city's
large docking bays is located.  The wall of the building on the east
side of the street, Docking Bay 87, is twenty feet thick to protect
the city from the blasts of leaving spacecraft.  From a domed building
on the west side of the street you can hear sounds of music... this
little building is the entrance to the underground Cantina.  Orleon
Lane runs north and south here.

Exits.Description:
You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

You see a large docking bay.  From there you can buy a way off this
dusty planet.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

You see a large, domed structure halfway buried into the earth.  From the
opening you hear loud piping music.  Some drunken stormtroopers stagger out
of the opening and walk down the alleyway.  This must be the galaxy-famous
Cantina.

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 87
rooms.Description:
Docking Bay 87 is a huge building with massively thick adobe walls.  Large
merchants use this bay because of the excellent security that the Imperial
bay down the street lends to the surrounding areas.  Many different types
of merchant vessels have been left here while their captains are out 
searching Mos Eisley for the products their employers require.

Exits.Description: Docking Bay 87 continues to your east.  Yes, it's REALLY that big.

You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

rooms.Name: Docking Bay 87
rooms.Description:
You come to the back wall of Docking Bay 87.  A large X-wing fighter
towers over you.  A smaller scientific research vehicle is also parked here.
After asking a few questions you learn that the X-wing is headed to the
swampy world of Dagobah for some sort of speciation survey.  The entrance
to Docking Bay 87 is to the west.

Exits.Description: Docking Bay 87 continues to your west.  Yes, it's REALLY that big.

rooms.Name: Orleon Lane
rooms.Description:
Blocky buildings of thick white adobe line both sides of the lane.  You
have come into a less traveled section of Mos Eisley.  The Regional
Government Offices are to the south and the Militia Headquarters are
in a large building to the east.  Few people in Mos Eisley would visit
these Imperial strong points if they have any alternative.  Orleon Lane
runs to the north here.

Exits.Description:
You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints.  Probably because of
the numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

You see a large, stone building with some local townsmen guarding the 
entrance of it.  A sign beside them lets you know this is the Tatooine
Militia Headquarters.

Before you stands a large, ornately decorated building.  A sign on the front
of it says:

                    Tatooine Regional Government Offices

                    Governer's Branch

rooms.Name: Tatooine Militia Headquarters
rooms.Description:
This is the headquarters of the Mos Eisley regiment of the Tatooine Militia.
The barracks are outside of the city itself, but this is a place where
citizens and statesmen can file complaints, requests and even enlist.
There are armed honor guards standing in the shadows, keeping the peace.

Exits.Description:
You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints. Probably because of the
numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

rooms.Name: Tatooine Regional Government Offices
rooms.Description:
In this building are the Regional Government Offices of this part of Tatooine.
All the official records for the region are kept here.  Territory population
maps and census records are kept on dirty antique shelves alone one wall.
A thin man stands behind the desk going over the deed to a remote farmstead.

Exits.Description:
You see a large, dusty road, covered with footprints. Probably becuase of the
numerous Stormtrooper patrols looking for some outlaw droids.

rooms.Name: Orleon Lane
rooms.Description: This space intentionally left blank.

rooms.Name: Inside the Cantina
rooms.Description:
Smoke swirls around your head as you descend the stairs into the
Cantina.  Woven grass mats hang on the walls by the stairs to help
keep out the heat.  You can leave the Cantina by going back up the
stairs or you can follow the sounds of drunken revelry coming from
the east into the bar.

Exits.Description:
You see a large open lobby and a bulky man who is sitting on a stool with his 
back leaning against the wall. He yells at some guy who is ahead of you, and 
leans over to press a button on a metal strip that surrounds the room.

Looking up, you are almost blinded by the flash of brilliant white light.
Tatooine's twin suns create such a glare off the sand that you can't really
tell much other than the fact that you are below ground.

rooms.Name: The Droid Detection Center
rooms.Description:
Across the threshold of the main room is a large, brightly polished 
strip of metal studded with bright flashing lights.  Sitting on a 
round wooden stool, leaning against the wall, is an extremely large
man.  He confronts the man in front of you, telling him, "Lose the
droids!  We don't serve their kind here."  You'd better not try to
get your droids past him... that sensor strip would play absolute
havoc with spell energies.

Exits.Description:
Many different aliens block your view, all that can really be said is that it
is vry crowded here. Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, you could
see what's in this place...

Many different aliens block your view, all that can really be said is that it
is very crowded here. Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, you 
could see what's in this place...

You see a drunk lying asleep on the steps. Behind him, you see a barely shut 
door, which keeps out the bright light from the twin suns of Tatooine.

rooms.Name: Inside the Cantina
rooms.Description:
You stand just inside the main room of the Cantina.  There are many
different species represented among the clientele, many of them you've
never seen before.  In the wall to the west is a small door.  You can
see the bar off through the smoke to the east.

Exits.Description:
Many different aliens block your view, all that can really be said is that it
is very crowded here. Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, you
could see what's in this place...

You see a large man, kicking a droid into a stasis field which proceeds in
blowing the droid apart.  This man means business, he does his job and he
does it quite well.  This must be the way out as you see people lining up
to get past this man inside the Cantina.

On the door is a sign:

                   CAUTION:  HIGH VOLTAGE!!
                        DO NOT ENTER!

Many different aliens block your view, all that can really be said is that
it's very crowded here.  Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, 
you could see what's in this place..

it's very crowded here.  Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, 
you could see what's in this place..

ExtraDescs.Description:
On the door is a sign:

                   CAUTION:  HIGH VOLTAGE!! 
                        DO NOT ENTER!

On the door is a sign:
                   CAUTION:  HIGH VOLTAGE!!
                        DO NOT ENTER!

rooms.Name: The Power Room
rooms.Description:
The sharp smell of ozone is thick in the air.  You have found the main 
generator powering the Cantina.  You had better leave... ozone has some
decidedly nasty effects on men.

Exits.Description:
Many different aliens block your view, all that can really be said is that it is
very crowded here. Perhaps if you pushed your way through the crowd, you could
see what's in this place...

rooms.Name: Among the Tables of the Cantina
rooms.Description:

rooms.Description:
You push your way through the employee's entrance and find yourself behind
the bar.  Underneath the top shelf are thousands upon thousands of 
multi-colored flasks filled with glowing liquids.  The bartender on duty
reaches under the bar and pulls out a flask filled with a bubbling, yellowish
green liquid.  He pours it into a glass and hands it to the customer on the
other side of the bar.

rooms.Name: The Cantina Offices
rooms.Description:
You see a small, cramped area decorated with only a small desk, lamp, chair,
and filing cabinet.  Scattered all over the desk are promisary notes, bills,
and numerous illegal-looking agreements.  All along the wall are various
gifts that Jabba has given to Chalamun, for providing a place for his
operatives to enjoy themselves and conduct business.  All in all, it's fairly
small for a wookie, and apparently Jabba seems to be skimming more profits
than Chalamun would like.

Exits.Description: You see a bunch of bottles and flasks stacked behind the bar.

rooms.Name: Inside the safe
rooms.Description:
This is the hotels large, walk in safe.  The management stores it's clients
valuable personal belongings here, as Mos Eisley is well known for it's
criminal element.  As you enter, the huge steel door swings silently shut
behind you.

rooms.Name: A path into the desert
rooms.Description:
This is where civilization ends, and the harsh reality of Tatooine's nature
takes over. For as far as the eye can see, there is nothing but endless seas
of sand. Way off in the distance you can see a tiny building which you surmise
to be Jabba's Desert Palace. Not too far off in the distance you can also see
a Jawa Sandcrawler treading its way through the dry desert. A sign nearby 
warns you not to wander aimlessly, as the Pit or Carkoon's Sarlaac has been 
known to devour many a reckless wanderer.

monotony that makes your brain hurt. Or may be it's hot sun that is making your

feel as if you could take a long nap right in this very spot.

the animal are various knives, probably serving as a cutting/skinning table
for the kitchen.

the dwelling warm on those cold desert nights.  To the north is the pantry

Jabba's Palace.

Jabba spends his time when he is aboard his Sail Barge, and it has been
furnished to fit his every whim.  Large, heavily grated windows cover
the side walls allowing the powerful criminal to survey the desert
wastes of Tatooine.  A small sliding hatch leads east.  A large door
in the west wall leads into the corridor.

Exits.Description: A small hatch leads into the bow of the vessel.

A large door opens into a dark corridor going into the aft part of the
vessel.

rooms.Name: The Corridor
rooms.Description:
The heat is stifling in the close confines of this dark corridor.
The grates over the windows are almost entirely closed.  A large door
at the east end leads into a private office.  Another large door at
the west end of the corridor leads into the pantry.  A wide stairwell
in the middle of the corridor goes up onto the deck.

Exits.Description: A large door leads east into Jabba's private office.
A large door leads into the pantry.
A small covered hatchway leads onto the deck of the ponderous Sail Barge.

rooms.Name: The Pantry
rooms.Description:
Huge cabinets of foodstuffs line the north and south walls of the
pantry.  From below you can hear the movements of the many creatures
held captive in the vast live well.  Jabba likes to eat, and this is
the best place on the Sail Barge to hold the food necessary to feed
him as much as he likes.  A large door leads east into a dark 
corridor and another door in the west wall goes into the kitchen.

Exits.Description: A door leads back into the corridor.
A door here leads into the galley.

rooms.Name: The Galley
rooms.Description:
The kitchen staff never rests in their unending quest to satisfy their
employer's enormous appetite.  The kitchen is extremely well equipped
and has an enormous pantry from which to draw meals.  Grimy sinks
and a sonic dishwasher serve to clean pots and pans.  A huge stove
lies up against the wall for the preparation of extremely large meals,
the kind especially common when Jabba and his lackeys are out on
one of their bizarre trips to feed the Sarlacc, with their festive
carnival atmosphere.  A door in the east wall leads into the pantry.
Loud shouts and gurgling laughter drift through the door to the west.

Exits.Description: A door leads into the dark pantry.

A large, swinging door leads back into a large room aft.  Singing and laughter
drifts through the door.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
The lobby is bright and airy.  Most of the large, heavily grated
windows have been left unshuttered.  There is a door to the east 
into the well equipped kitchen of the Sail Barge.  To the west an
enormous room stretches the remaining length of the Sail Barge.
Dirty and misshapen thieves and bounty hunters of every type crowd
the immense banquet room and observation cabin of Jabba's Sail Barge.

Exits.Description: A large, swinging door leads into the galley.

A large number of huge, filthy bounty hunters and smugglers laughs and
enjoys the festivities.

rooms.Name: The Observation Cabin and Banquet Room
rooms.Description:
The heavy smell of intoxicants and smoke fills the air.  A swirling 
gray fog obscures your view and cuts visibility to a scant handful of
meters.  Alien shapes surround you, some unbelievably large and still
others warped and twisted into mocking silhouettes too bizarre to 
describe.  You are in the immense observation cabin and banquet room
of Jabba the Hutt's floating Sail Barge.  To the east is the lobby and
the banquet room stretches off into the smoke to the west.

Exits.Description:
A large number of huge, filthy bounty hunters and smugglers laughs and enjoys

rooms.Name: The Rounded Bow Section of the Deck
rooms.Description:
You are standing at the front most part of the upper deck on Jabba's
Sail Barge.  A waist high railing runs along the outside edge of the
deck, offering passengers at least the illusion of safety.  Along 
the deck to the west you can see several large masts and quite a few
bounty hunters.

Exits.Description:
You see a bunch of various bounty hunters, scattered in a chaotic array
some firing at the parked Sail Skiff, others dealing with disturbances
on deck.

rooms.Name: On the Deck of Jabba's Sail Barge
rooms.Description:
Waist high railings run along the sides of the Sail Barge's deck.
Bounty hunters yell with surprise at your presence, they don't seem
to like you.  Just beyond the sides of the Barge you can see the 
edges of the huge sails.  A hatch opens downward into the interior
of the Sail Barge.  To the east you can see the front end of the
deck.  To the west several masts sprout ponderously from the
blasted metal deck and hold huge sails secure.

rooms.Name: On the Deck of Jabba's Sail Barge
rooms.Description:
Waist high railings run along the sides of the Sail Barge's deck.
The idling roar of the Sail Barge's immense engines can be heard
from just below.  Jabba's Sail Barge might look ponderous, but it
can move very fast if it really has to.  A thin staircase runs up
the side of a boxy structure which stretches across the deck west
of here.  To the east you can see several huge masts and a large
deck-mounted blaster cannon.

Exits.Description:
You see a bunch of various bounty hunters, scattered in a chaotic array
some firing at the parked Sail Skiff, others dealing with disturbances
on deck.

Up a small set of stairs you see the top of the Observation Deck where you
can survey the whole Barge.

rooms.Name: The Privacy Lounge
rooms.Description:
You have entered Jabba's personal privacy lounge.  He likes to watch
from here while his men feed hapless prisoners to the Sarlacc.  Thick
smoke swirls around your head and makes it difficult to see.  An
enormous chair, built to hold Jabba's immense bulk, dominates the
center of the room.  The thick metal grates over the viewing ports
are most of the way open here.  A wide staircase along the west wall
leads down into the banquet room and observation cabin.

Exits.Description:
A large number of huge, filthy bounty hunters and smugglers laughs and
enjoys the festivities.

rooms.Name: The Observation Deck
rooms.Description:
Waist high railings run along three sides of this elevated platform.
From here you have a wonderful view of the deadly spectacle.  The
loud hum of the idling engines shakes the deck below your feet.  A
narrow staircase leads off the east end of the platform and onto the
rest of the deck.

Exits.Description:
Below you, you see the Top Deck of Jabba's Sail Barge.  Various bounty
hunters are scrambling around amidst the ensuing chaos..

rooms.Name: A Guest Room
rooms.Description:
A large bed lies up against the north wall of this small private
room.  Jabba the Hutt houses his most respected guests in dirty
rooms like this one.  A large desk sits against the wall next to
the bed.  A sturdy door leads east.

rooms.Name: A Guest Room
rooms.Description:
A large bed lies up against the east wall of this small private
room.  Jabba the Hutt houses his most respected guests in dirty
rooms like this one.  A large desk sits against the wall next to
the bed.  A bowl of dried fruit sits in the middle of the desk.
A sturdy door leads north.

rooms.Name: Outside the Rancor Pit
rooms.Description:
A huge ditanium gate is here keeping the horrors that lurk within this
cavern inside.  Savage snarling can be heard from within, and you smell a
repugnant smell coming from the other side of the gate.  Whatever is trapped
in there, it doesn't seem like a bright idea to go inside and upset it.

rooms.Name: The Rancor Pit
rooms.Description:
All around you is darkness, the only light comes from the ceiling grating
which is about 25 feet in the air.  From within the shadows you hear a sinister
hissing, and boulders falling from that direction.  It appears that your 
arrival has awakened something horrid within there, and it sees you as its
next lunch.  The darkness coalesces as your eyes adjust, just in time to see
the menacing form of a dreaded Rancor monster lurching towards you...

rooms.Name: The Stage (starring the Max Rebo Band)
rooms.Description:
Stuck in a small alcove, Max Rebo and his band being to jam and play
music for the evil Jabba.. the pay is high, the publicity is great, and most
of all, they get to live when the show is over...

rooms.Description:

music for the evil Jabba.. the pay is high, the publicity is great, and most

rooms.Name: The Pit of Carkoon - Beneath Jabba's Sail Barge
rooms.Description:
You are standing directly beneath Jabba's Large Sail Barge.  Above you on
a smaller sail skiff, you see Han Solo and Chewbacca leaning over the
edge trying to rescue Lando Calrissian from being eaten by the hungry
Sarlaac Pit.  A small, yet sturdy service ladder leads up onto the
main deck of Jabba's Barge.

rooms.Name: On the Deck of the Small Sail Skiff
rooms.Description:
The skiff resembles a smaller version of Jabba's larger Sail Barge.  Currently
this skiff is parked alongside the Barge and hovering above the deadly Sarlaac
Pit.  It's apparent that someone will be fed today to the Pit, perhaps one of
Jabba's smugglers he's disappointed with.

Exits.Description:
You see some Skiff Guards trying to stop the ensuing chaos happening on the s
skiff.

Down a cable hanging over the side of the skiff you see the large open maw 
of the deadly Sarlaac Pit creature.

rooms.Name: On the Small Sail Skiff
rooms.Description:
A large plank to the north would allow you to jump onto the main deck
of Jabba's Sail Barge.  Small laser blasters are mounted on a railing 
surrounds the Skiff.  Speed is this vehicle's primary concern, as you 
can tell by the large engine and control panel.

Exits.Description:
At the end of a long plank, you could probably jump onto the deck of Jabba's
Sail Barge.

You see a blind Han Solo stumbling around while Chewbacca is protecting his
friend at the other end of the Sail Skiff.

Uh, what may I ask are you doing looking up from a death-trap area? I really 
hope that you're an immortal or a very high level mortal doing this, otherwise,
find the nearest Computer Confession terminal and report yourself for 
immediate and lasting vaporization... Thank you, have a nice day, and 
remember, the Computer is your Friend!

rooms.Name: The Garage
rooms.Description:
You have entered the half buried garage of a desert homestead.  Piles
of broken and salvageable equipment lie in neat stacks along the walls.
In one corner near the door a battered Skyhopper has been partly
covered by a dusty sheet of plastic.  A large oil bath sits in the
middle of the room next to a large, sturdy work bench.

Exits.Description: The desert sun shines brightly through the garage door.

rooms.Name: The Courtyard
rooms.Description:
You are in a large pit that serves as the central courtyard of a modest
desert homestead.  A thin stairway winds its way up one side and out onto
the desert plain above.  A large moisture vaporator stands in the middle
of the courtyard and hums quietly.

Exits.Description: Pleasant smells drift from the open door of the kitchen.
A staircase spirals up onto the desert wasteland above.

rooms.Name: The Kitchen
rooms.Description:
The kitchen is brightly lit and pleasant aromas of meals past linger in
the cool air.  A large food processor sits on the sandstone counter
and a small stove sits against the west wall.

Exits.Description: The sun shines brightly onto the courtyard.

rooms.Name: Inside the Access Tube - Sandcrawler First Floor
rooms.Description:
Piles upon piles of scattered junk lay everywhere.  Dimly lit, you can
barely see across the room.  Droids in various states of operation lie
around with restraining bolts on, hoping to escape their enslavement.
Numerous junk items lie on the ground, most of which don't work.
The Jawa may be scavengers, but the word kleptomaniacs comes to mind when
seeing the contents of this room.

Exits.Description:
Through the cluttered doorway, you see a roomful of junk. Piled up to the 
edges of the walls, the darkened room is easily a disaster area. Various 
droids and machinery lie on the ground in various states of repair.

Through the cluttered doorway, you see a roomful of junk.  Piled up to the
edges of the walls, the darkened room is easily a disaster area.  Various
droids and machinery lie on the ground in various states of repair.

Down the access tube, you can see the hot searing sand of Tatooine's
desert.

rooms.Name: North End of the Sandcrawler - Second Floor
rooms.Description:
Piles upon piles of scattered junk lay everywhere.  Dimly lit, you can
barely see across the room.  Droids in various states of operation lie
around with restraining bolts on, hoping to escape their enslavement.
Numerous junk items lie on the ground, most of which don't work.
The Jawa may be scavengers, but the word kleptomaniacs comes to mind when
seeing the contents of this room.

Exits.Description:
You see a large control room where two Jawas control the Sandcrawler. You can
also see a large window looking out over the land.

Through the cluttered doorway, you see a roomful of junk. Piled up to the edges
of the walls, the darkened room is easily a disaster area. Various droids and
machinery lie on the ground in various states of repair.

rooms.Name: Sandcrawler Control Room - Second Floor
rooms.Description:
A large blastshield window covers the northern part of the room.  Through
the shield you can see a small water vaporator farming community.  Off in the
distance you see the vile gangster, Jabba the Hutt's Palace.  You also
notice his Sail Barge cruising beside the Pit of Carkoon, it appears Jabba
is in the mood for an execution today.  Currently the Sandcrawler is
treading slowly onwards towards a small home near Beggar's Canyon, it
must be the home of the crazy old hermit, Ben Kenobi.  The Jawa at the 
control panel punches a few buttons and brings up a map showing the 
location of all the surrounding major points of interest, such as Mos
Eisley Spaceport.

Exits.Description:
Through the cluttered doorway, you see a roomful of junk. Piled up to the edges
of the walls, the darkened room is easily a disaster area. Various droids and
machinery lie on the ground in various states of repair.

rooms.Name: At the Top of the Access Ramp
rooms.Description:
Florescent lights run along the top length of the ceiling lighting up the
room.  The whole interior of the ship is paved with metal accessways.  Small
red lights blink every 3 feet to let you know the Shuttle is in flight and
fully operational.

Exits.Description: You see a holodeck chess board along with various other entertaining things.
Various items fill the room, from spices to numerous other supplies.
You see a room full of scattered tools and mechanical looking objects.

Down at the bottom of the ramp you see the planet's surface.  Hot, arid
air drifts in counteracting the cool air-conditioned room where you are now.

rooms.Name: Starboard Cargo Hold
rooms.Description:
This room is used mainly for the storing of large objects.  Currently there
are boxes of Correlian Spice, a box with blasters in it, droid parts, and
heavy machinery of unknown purpose.  The boxes are neaty arranged and packed
so tight that you can only manage to pull one out to examine the contents.

Exits.Description: You see the hatchway where passengers enter/leave the shuttle.

rooms.Name: Engineering Section
rooms.Description:
All over the floor lie scattered tools of numerous types, from hydrospanners
to laser-wrenches.  The room overall seems grimey as you see greasy gobs 
splattered on certains parts of the floor.  You heard the faint distant humming
of the engines coming from behind the large control panel before you.  
Numerous lights dot the panel, and you see the controls for the hyperspace
system here, with the wires apparently severed beyond repair.

Exits.Description:
You see the top of the access hatch where passengers depart from/arrive to
the shuttle.

rooms.Name: Forward Cargo Hold
rooms.Description:
You can barely enter the room here as it is completely packed to the ceiling
full of large metal crates containing who knows what.  You have no more than
two feet in front of you to move around in.  Seeing nothing of interest,
you decide to turn back the way you came.

Exits.Description: You see a large room taken up mostly by a large holodeck chess board.

rooms.Name: Inside the Cockpit of the Imperial Shuttle Tydirium
rooms.Description:
This small compartment area has seats for about 4 people and allows access to
the various flashing lights and controls that surround the walls and ceiling.
Currently there is a flamboyant alien-looking man sitting in the chair
frantically trying to figure out the controls.  Suddenly from out of the
blue you see a starship streak past the shuttle barely avoiding clipping it.
You can't help but stare at the now-empty viewport, watching out for another
close call like that.

Exits.Description: You see a large room taken up mostly by a large holodeck chess board.

rooms.Name: Recreation Room
rooms.Description:
Dominating the center of the room, is a large holodeck chess board similar
to the ones that are equipped aboard every Correlian Space Cruiser.  The
game seems to be broke, as its continually playing the same move over and
over.  Perhaps the last person to play was a Wookie disgruntled at having
lost.  A long bunk lies in the corner of the room as well as various little
recreational tools for relieving stress.

Exits.Description:
You see a two-headed man at the controls of the ship, who periodically 
tosses his hands into the air in frustration and grumbles.
You see the hatchway where passengers enter/leave the Shuttle.
You see a lavishly decorated room with carpeting and soft beds.
You see another room full of various boxes and crates, piled ceiling high.

rooms.Name: Passenger Bay/Crew Quarters
rooms.Description:
The first thing you notice upon entering this room is the warmth coming from
heater vents along the floor.  Plush carpeting covers the floor completely
offering something a little less cold and metallic to walk on.  A viewport
to the east shows a flying ship speeding past you into hyperspace.  All in
all it's a very relaxing environment, one which you could rest and sleep in.

Exits.Description: You see a large room taken up mostly by a large holodeck chess board.

rooms.Name: Inside an Escape Pod
rooms.Description:
Small.  Very small.  Perhaps if someone didn't kill the pilot you wouldn't
have to resort to taking an Escape Pod back to the Temple.  Around you lie
the barest essentials in case something wrong goes on turning re-entry.
